          "body": "Verses 12-13 are not a free-standing doctrinal statement about Scripture; they are the *teeth* of the warning. The same word that announced the rest will judge those who refused it. *Living and active* (zōn kai energēs) — Scripture has its own verbs. *Sharper than any two-edged sword* — surgical, not blunt. *Piercing as far as the division of soul and spirit, joints and marrow* — reaching the deepest seams of human personhood, where self-deception hides. *Able to judge the thoughts and intentions of the heart* — a courtroom verb (*kritikos*). And then 4:13 personalizes: *no creature is hidden from His sight; all things are open and laid bare to the eyes of Him with whom we have to do*. The image *laid bare* (*tetrachelismena*) is debated — perhaps the wrestler's throat-grip, perhaps the sacrificial animal's bent neck before the knife. Either way: God sees, God judges, and the same Scripture that warned you will testify against you. The verse is terrifying — by design."
